caption: Had a poor experience here. Rude service. Will never return.  UPDATE: This experience is from 2019. The staff were incredibly and necessarily rude after being a repeat customer for over 1 year. I would not recommend spending your money at this business.
Love the place!
Another super cozy place from 16OC folks. Great atmosphere, music, specialty sandwiches, and the staff are  terrific too. Will def be back again!

This roast beef...the tang of marinated pepper perfectly balances the rich umami of the juicy beef and rich white cheddar. And the red pepper aoli is the perfect topper. Wow. I can't wait to try more of the menu. Get over here and put a party in your mouth!
great place to chill and grab a quick drink after work.
Friendly staff, delicious drinks, sandwiches and salads.
A good local sandwich shop and coffee stop
Really nice spot. AMAZING chai! I had to get 2 cups because it was so good. Nice atmosphere. Gets crazy busy during lunch time, for good reason
Excellent place for morning coffee with friendly staff and high quality sandwich options.
Please come and enjoy awesome food and amazing staff that  nailed a Paloma for me and my gf!
Great Service, Awesome food and drinks, They're open for breakfast and drinks after work.

I love this place, it’s become a frequent lunch spot. Their sandwiches are great, every single one I’ve tasted, although I almost always go for the grilled cheese because it’s simply fantastic.  It’s a fun place to hang out for a while, and a Friday lunch-time Bloody Mary has never hurt anyone, right? ;)

First off, I’m vegetarian. I ordered the “breakfast Sando” and when he asked me if I wanted to add anything to it I said no, because I don’t eat meat, and he told me I “wasn’t allowed to order it without meat because they were running low on eggs.” Someone please tell me how that makes sense. Didn’t end up ordering anything and will never come back.
Cool place with great service. Nice selection of sandwiches.

Nice place with good vibe and great service. Also love the decor.  I tried the Aviator cocktail and the melt tuna. The sandwich was way too salty and not very good in my opinion, but the drink was amazing.  Can be very busy during lunch time.
Absolutely fantastic – a stand-out in a city with 800,000 coffee shops. Great food, strong coffee, knock-you-down cocktails...need I say more?
Really yummy breakfast sandwich. Cute decor. Not too loud at lunch

Always come to the Ruin Daily for a good sandwich. This time, I was introduced to a Perrin Brewing Company Black Ale- the chocolatey, coffee flavors of a stout or Porter, but not as heavy. One of my new favorites. They also have good sweets- not a bad way to gain 40 lbs.
Great sandwiches and coffee. Haven't gone there any time other than lunch hour, but it's always fun when I do.
Lots of fun and a great selection of craft beer. Servers were attentive and the beer prices were very good for Chicago
Great sandwiches & beer selection
Solo dinner. Awesome sandwiches. I had the veggie and a beer. Cool, comfortable and clean. Great service service and well priced. What more can you ask for?

I ordered a simple tuna salad sandwich, and I was genuinely disgusted. The bread was soaked in grease with a layer of burnt, crusted cheese sitting on both sides. Very unhealthy. Also had a turkey club, and the meat was very cheap quality.

The Ruin Daily seems to be a hit or miss. A lot of my coworkers love it, I’ve given it a chance many times and can’t bring myself to give it a thumbs up. Sandwiches are expensive and below average. I’ve found chicken cartilage in them several times and just couldn’t finish my meal.  On a side note, their donuts are delicious! Too bad they don’t make them themselves. Drinks are good, but once again, expensive. Not sure how a sandwich shop makes better drinks than sandwiches to be honest.  I tried giving these guys a chance but unfortunately it’s always been a let down.  Luckily, there are plenty of other sandwich shops in the area to choose from that are tastier and cheaper.
The best place in the area for a quick breakfast, lunch and after work drinks (you can’t beat the drinks here after work!). The service is awesome and the food is tasty. Check it out!
Loved the wrap sandwich. Positive atmosphere. Enjoyed a glass of water from the water dispenser.

Extremely worth it. Got the Cuban sandwich & I took my sweet time savoring every spice & sauce - their style is authentic & made with love. I would recommend anyone stopping through Chicago to seek out this classy joint 😍
This place is legit! Attention to detail with all food and drinks. That's why they're all so flavorful. Do yourself a favor and become a regular.
Always the best service from Chelsea and Koji! 5 stars all around!

Always great, fresh food. The Cuban sandwich should be in everyone's mouth presently. Awesome homemade fruit yogurt as a solid breakfast choice. Service can be a little slow,  but it's 100% because they are taking the time to give you a quality product.

The service was good and there is a nice ambiance inside. I was however, very disappointed in my sandwich. I got the Chipotle Chicken, which came out to a little over $17 with no additions...just the sandwich and a tip. i was told it would be a large portion so I agreed to pay the amount. When I received the sandwich the contents were very skimpy. I would've been more fulfilled getting a 6 inch sub from Subway. The sandwich didn't taste like anything chipotle either. It was basically pulled chicken and bell peppers. The price and portion size wasn't worth it.

They make some very tasty sandwiches, but I'm often very disappointed in the amount of contents.  Especially given the price.  Their promotional picture of the sandwich rarely looks like the real thing.
The sandwich I had was great! I had never seen this place before, it doesn't stand out much but from the outside but was quite a good lunch!
Great sandwiches
Nice sandwich.  A bit on the pricey side for a sandwich

Great sandwiches and beer. I came on a Tuesday and got to draw and doodle while we ate. I spun the wheel and got a free beer! I had the tuna melt and it was delicious! Great service too! Really cool atmosphere and we stayed longer to draw and drink.
It confusing sometimes
Great good and good price
The bahn mi sandwich I had failed big time.  It was loaded with BBQ sauce and pickled jalapenos. Drinks were good and so was the service.
Great staff and great space. Easy to get to from the West Loop. I enjoyed my breakfast sandwich too.
Good food.  Very hipsterish
I LOVE this place! The sandwich sizes are huge and I personally am in love with the square home made donuts. You really can't go wrong with anything on the menu here. I highly recommend!

I had the Cuban sandwich. Was more or less a ham and pork sandwich with a pickle on top .Tasted okay but was very small for $10 (looked to be about 2oz of meat). Wouldn't recommend coming here hungry.
Got the wrong order, food was ok.
the order fell short for me. A team lunch was provided for 5. 3 liked 2 disliked. Will be going back to try other menu items to confirm.
Great options for drinks and love the homemade pickles and outdoor seating.
Had a catered lunch from here and it was delicious. Really enjoyed it. Also got a coffee in here, and was great. Wonderful branding as well.
Great place to grab a breakfast sandwich if you work in the area. Everything I have tried is delicious and it has great happy hours!
The wine is overpriced but the food is fantastic!
A lunch favorite, just know that all the sandwiches are very heavy

Live the place - love the vibe - love the food ... You have to catch their daily specials - you never know what fabulous new favorite my show up.  o of the best meatloaf sandwiches to ever hit a lunch special! Never disappointed.
Great drinks, great environment. Unassuming yet impressive.
I got a mushroom melt which was good had to wait 10- 15 min to get my food though so not the fastest place.
Very warm environment employees are kind and attentive
Was passing through Chicago on a layover. Staff was very friendly, meatballs were delicious!
Long wait but good food.

Great sandwich shop with pastries, cookies and a full bar (!)  The sandwiches are well crafted with fresh and good quality ingredients.  The coffee is fresh and flavorful.  Staff are great - friendly and attentive.  Definitely worth multiple visits.  The only request I have is that I'd like more breakfast sandwich options.     🤓👍

The place has a great atmosphere and above average food. The sandwiches are pretty good, I don't care for the sides but I know my friends love them.  The cocktails are $10, which is pretty good considering the area. The aviator is my favorite.

Great place for some pretty delicious sandwiches and a coffee or cocktail (though I've yet to try their beverages). I love the atmosphere and the staff is very friendly. However, it takes a lot longer than expected to get your food, which on a limited lunchhour timeframe can be a little troublesome.
I like the salads and some sandwiches. I found their pastrami on rye to be greasy AF.

The sandwiches are usually good but the soup was not good. I think a little more attention to detail would help a lot, the little things aren't correct like my "special sauce" was a think paste of cocktail sauce. Hopefully my next visit will be better
I had the Cuban sandwich and a dirty martini and both were phenomenal. Lovely atmosphere.  This place is a gem. Highly recommend!
Fantastic food and drink select with a really creative menu. Did not once get attacked by a bear. Definitely a place worth visiting!
Yummy sandwiches. Loved the egg,cheese with eggplant sandwich

The atmosphere is great and the staff are nice. The food on the other hand is mediocre. This place is down the street from my building so I wish the food was better because I go out to eat everyday and I would this to be my local “go to” place.
Ruben is delicious. Great place for quick lunch.
Sandwiches were good but nothing special.
Nice bar can be a bit loud. Has trivia every Tuesday.
Ruin Daily always delivers great sandwiches. Recently signed up for the R&D club to get deals on their weekly specials. I try to come once a week for lunch if I can.
The best tuna melt ever. It's a lunch-time staple around my office.
Great quality coffee, food and drink!
Very solid place in the West loop, especially after work when there isn't much else in the vicinity
Creat gourmet sandwiches and excellent service
Good sandwiches but long wait for takeout.
No vegan options.
Great service and relaxing environment!  Refreshing beverages.  The Aviator has given me a new found appreciation for Sloe Gin.
Original and crafty sandwiches and drinks.  Go out of your way to eat and drink here.
Great food and service. Would recommend highly
Easy going place with a clean look. Good for grabbing a drink with friends from the office.
Great food and very friendly staff. Try out the corned beef hash or biscuits and gravy. They also have a full bar selection and other great drinks like Mint Mocha.
Love this neighborhood cafe/bar. The staff is very good. Sandwiches are yummy and the cocktail menu is good!
Great coffee, environment and staff worth walking a couple of blocks to visit.

The craft cocktails are excellent and the sandwiches and chips are icing on the cake (though the menu features no actual cake). Can get a bit crowded and noisy during lunch and happy hour, but really nice during the non-prime times.
Coffee, sandwiches, cocktails.
Whoa God that was good! Best roast beef sandwich I've ever had. That potato salad too, blasphemy! So so good. I'll be back for more, with new reviews.
Food was eh.
Yum coffee and food. A bit on the pricey side however. Their seasonal smoothie in the summer is delicious!
Free WiFi and super helpful staff. I also thought their ham and cheese sandwich was really good for a coffee shop.
Great spot for sandwiches and cocktails. They make their own pickles which are really tasty. Try the Tuna melt... One of the best in the city.

Finally ...Life in the dead space where the West Loop and the South Loop converge! The "go to" I've been waiting for! Diagonally across from my apt with everything you need - coffee, delicious sandwiches, food to go, beer, wine, great music, excellent service and friendly staff. Let's hope they decide to extend their hours once they see how busy they are and how much we need them ...Thank You!
Sandwiches so good there's no time for pictures. Try "The Little Magician" or the "Gym Shoe" both great sandwiches. Great coffee from Metric Coffee out of Chicago.
